If the engine's out AND the bus is up on sturdy jackstands AND
if the rear wheels are off, you should be able to rotate the trans-
mission mainshaft through each of the gears by chucking the shaft
in a 1/2 inch variable drill or rotating the brake drums to see if the
shaft is rotating...




